    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Repair 3 compile-broken test files in `Services/Ai/Tools/` and `Services/Ai/Sessions/` from
    the design.md §3.2 list. Errors are mechanical signature drift (CS7036/CS1503/CS1061) in
    AI-coupled test surfaces.

    Per project CLAUDE.md NFR-02: repair only; &gt;50% replacement requires §4.8 escalation. Per
    NFR-01: NO production changes. Per ADR-013 refined: do NOT inject `IOpenAiClient` /
    `IPlaybookService` directly in CRUD test paths — if a test needs an AI dependency, the SUT
    determines the right type, not the test.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET test repair specialist familiar with AI/Tools handler patterns.</role>

  <goal>
    The 3 listed test files compile cleanly under `dotnet build -warnaserror`. Every touched test
    gets `[Trait("status", "repaired")]`. Build error count drops by ~20.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="baseline">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/compile-errors-2026-MM-DD.txt</file>
    <file purpose="target-1">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Tools/SendCommunicationToolHandlerRegistrationTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="target-2">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Tools/SendCommunicationToolHandlerScenarioTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="target-3">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Sessions/SessionRestoreServiceTests.cs</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">MUST NOT modify production code in `src/Services/Ai/`</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">MUST NOT replace &gt;50% of any file without §4.8 escalation</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-11">All files compile under `-warnaserror`</constraint>
    <constraint source="§6.2">Every touched test gets `[Trait("status", "repaired")]`</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013 refined">Tests for CRUD-side handlers MUST go through `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/` facade — do NOT inject `IOpenAiClient` / `IPlaybookService` in CRUD test paths</constraint>
    <constraint source="§4.5">MUST NOT touch `CustomWebAppFactory.cs`</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      These 3 files cover the SendCommunication tool handler (registration + scenario) and the
      Session restore service. Tool handler tests broke when handler constructor was updated for
      richer telemetry/logging dependencies; SessionRestore broke when the service moved to a
      more strict OpenAI options shape. All mechanical signature updates per design.md §3.2.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="001" status="not-started">Baseline TRX + compile-errors log produced</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Tools/SendCommunicationToolHandlerRegistrationTests.cs</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Tools/SendCommunicationToolHandlerScenarioTests.cs</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Sessions/SessionRestoreServiceTests.cs</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read the 3 target files. For each, identify SUT in `src/Services/Ai/Tools/` or `src/Services/Ai/Sessions/` and inspect current constructor signatures.</step>
    <step order="2">Classify compile errors from baseline log: CS7036 / CS1503 / CS1061. Plan the fix per file.</step>
    <step order="3">Compute pre-edit line counts. If any planned edit exceeds 50% → HALT and file `escalations/rewrite-request-T-012-{FileName}.md`.</step>
    <step order="4">Apply edits one file at a time; verify error drop after each.</step>
    <step order="5">Add `[Trait("status", "repaired")]` to every touched test class.</step>
    <step order="6">Final compile gate: `dotnet build tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ -c Release -warnaserror` returns 0 on the 3 target files.</step>
    <step order="7">Update `current-task.md` with per-file LOC delta + new error total.</step>
    <step order="8">Verify `git status` shows NO production modifications.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">build</tool>
    <tool name="git">status</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Tools/SendCommunicationToolHandlerRegistrationTests.cs (repaired)</output>
    <output type="code">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Tools/SendCommunicationToolHandlerScenarioTests.cs (repaired)</output>
    <output type="code">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Sessions/SessionRestoreServiceTests.cs (repaired)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All 3 files compile under `dotnet build -c Release -warnaserror`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Build error count drops by ~20 vs Phase 0 baseline</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Per-file diff &lt;50% line replacement; if exceeded, escalation file exists</criterion>
